Some glory in their birth, some in their skill,
And some in patient hope, their hearts kept still;
For every crown and laurel, shining bright,
There stands a dreamer waiting in the night.

Not all must ride the chariot of fame,
Nor carve in stone a widely honored name;
For glory blooms in many quiet ways—
A word of kindness, or a hand that stays.

So let them boast who win the world’s acclaim;
I’ll seek my joy where love and peace remain.
